'''
There may be times when you want to specify a type on to a variable.
This can be done with casting.
'''
x = int(1)   # x will be 1
y = int(2.8) # y will be 2
z = int("3") # z will be 3

m = float("3")   # z will be 3.0
n = str(2)    # y will be '2'

print(int(35.88)) #35
print(float(35)) #35.0
print(str(35.82)) #35.82
